The European inflation slid into the food
The rapid inflation, registered in the area of euro, must in the first place to vertiginous growth of the price of food products.
The increase in prices in the month of November has been over what is expected in the 13 countries of the euro zone, registering - after the 2.6% of the month of October - an annual inflation of 3.1% - the Statistical Office of the Union with headquarters in Luxembourg.
The official forecasts only gave as likely a 3% - the Bloomberg.
The European Central Bank (ECB), in contrast to the banks North American, British and Canadian, not to cut the basic interest, under the pretext that the decrease, along with rising prices of raw materials and the reduction of the lay-off, would cause a spiral of inflation.
The ECB wants to maintain the rate of inflation below, but at least some of the two per cent.
As an observer, the ECB is found in the catch 22: "It is necessary to negotiate" on inflation to subsequently does not have to intervene in this matter.
The inflation of 3.3%, registered in Germany, broke the record of twelve years; as in Spain increased of 3.6 at 4.1%.
Inflation is off in the area of the euro as a result of the galloping nutritional and energy.
The prices at the end of the wheat increased by 88%, and also the listing of the soya reached its highest level since 1973.
Equally, it was necessary to pay a lot more in the 2007 for the vegetable oil and for the milk products.
The price of crude oil in the world market increased this year in 52%, reaching since last month the black gold 100 dollars a barrel.
According to the ECB, inflation in 2008 will of 2.1% today to 2.5%, in exchange for the 2009 will diminish as to 1.9.
According to the analysts, annual inflation will stay in the next three or four months about 3%, but the annual average rate will be 2.1%.
At the same time, it is expected that during the year 2008 the ECB reduces twice the interest rates.
Gallup foresees a governmental crisis
After a long stagnation, for the beginning of December, the support of the alliance of democratic youngsters increased significantly, reaching its maximum level since 2002, while the Gallup never before experienced such a low level - a 13% - in the case of the Socialists.
The difference in the case of the electorate certain parties - due to the greater firmness of the electorate of the opposition - would mean a support of more than two thirds (71%), with the support of a fifth for the Socialists (20%).
According to the survey, the democratic forum and the alliance of the free democrats do not reach the necessary limit to have any parliamentary: its support in the whole of the population is two per cent.
Among the electorate sure there is a one per cent of supporters in both sides.
The economic environment continued to deteriorate even in comparison with the previous lowest point - it has never been so high, 41% of the proportion of those who considered to be especially the economic situation of the country, while another 46% believes that the situation is quite bad.
The families, after the most encouraging expectations of the spring and summer, are now more pessimistic about the change in its own economic situation.
As for the next year, the majority of the population is provided with the deterioration of the situation and only one-tenth expects an improvement.
In the month of December, 71% of the consulted, superior to any previous survey of Gallup, thought that the President of the government rather desempena badly that well its functions.
The 13% of the consulted trust or trust much Ferenc Gyurcsány, while Viktor orbán counts on the support of the 38% of the consulted.
54% of the population did not trust the head of government at all and 27% do not trust in the President of the Alliance for the democratic young people.
One of the indicators of the configuration of the political situation is that, what proportion of the society thinks that it is possible to control the dissatisfaction experienced in front of the person of the head of government without a change of government.
While that after the disturbances in October of last year a 35% considered that it would be desirable to keep the power to the government and to the head of government, at the moment, this proportion is only 20%, while the relative majority (33%) believes that the only solution is the holding of new elections.
The interest in the referendum is characterized by the fact that 60% of respondents to the question on the participation replied that he would probably and another 20% said that is likely to participate.
To comparative way, in the "general elections to be celebrated this Sunday" would surely only 55 per cent of the population and another 15% believes its participation probable. By means of the current intentions of the voters there is no doubt of the result of the referendum.
A 74% of the population would disapprove of the payment of the rights of studies, 79% of the service of medical consultations and 84% of the hospital attention.
If we observe these proportions between the participants in the referendum, 81, 84 and 89% of the voters would reject the introduction of the rights of studies, the payment for the medical consultations and of the hospital attention.
The most expensive is the auchan, Tesco has quintupled their prices
