In many hospitals are saved with disinfectants
This year there have been registered in the hospitals several thousands of infections produced in the first place by the illegal application of antibiotics.
The circumstances of hygiene in the hospitals, the overcrowding of nets, and the overload of staff do not facilitate the control of infection - the department of the national Center of.
In many hospitals are saved even with disinfectants.
Not long ago has been diagnosed infection with the in the department of traumatología of hospital.
In a man hospitalized after a serious accident was detected the presence of the bacteria resistant to antibiotics.
The patient was isolated.
The same type of infection took place in this same hospital at the beginning of the year.
A wounded of a serious car accident they discharged the hospital and the same patient soon had to go back to the hospital as a result of the infection with the, and since then it has not been possible to make an important operation by the presence of the bacterium in their bodies.
Until 10 December of this year have been registered in the national system cases of infection hospital produced by agents - said, Doctor - chief of head of the national Center of.
This means that in the hospitals for certain there has been the number of infections produced by agents, the rest do not have information.
Nearly two thirds of infection (683 cases) must be at the, that is to say to the aureus, resistant to the meticilina-oxacilina.
A third of the human beings carried in its nose the bacteria of the aureus (Ltd) without causing any illness.
The infections produced by the SA (e.g.: inflammation of the throat, amigdalitis infections, infections of) react to antibiotics and are easy to treatment.
However, once it is applied exaggerated or illegally to antibiotics, the bacteria which usually react to antibiotics, transformed into bacteria very resistant to antibiotics and contaminate quickly in inadequate hospital conditions.
They can cause serious hospital infections, for example infections of or septicemia in the first place to patients with temporary or chronic immunodeficiency, to patients with the Agency weakened, old or people of little weight.
In view of the hospital doctor - there is nothing special in the infection of the, these infections are daily in the hospitals.
The infection must not be confused with the epidemic, the only is absent - he said - where its presence is not examined.
Resistant to antibiotics
"these patients are isolated, the staff takes care of in gloves of rubber and mask and antibiotics adapted to their treatment" - said.
The patients are examined previously to verify the presence of the in their bodies, but even so it is possible to avoid the infection in all cases.
It is fashionable to take samples
It would be possible to prevent the hospital infections of the in the majority of cases, but the current national hospital circumstances do not facilitate for the prevention of the training and the infection with the pathogenic agents - States.
As this infection fundamentally takes place in hospitals and homes of old, hospitals, should examine the patients and isolate immediately to the ill that they go in their bodies on the.
However, in the Hungarian hospitals is not fashion the capture of exhibitions.
This fact is also due to the fact that the national box of health, not to finance these medical examinations.
So that the majority of cases they come to light public when it is already produced infections of the visible in the patient - the department of the Center.
The European Union makes rigorous charges for the use of antibiotics in human medicine, and there are also national directives to treat the pathological infections and pictures.
It is necessary to get in which the therapy with antibiotic is directed, that is to say, it would make microbiological examinations to prevent that takes place in the face of resistance to the medicines, but the hospitals do not always comply with this demand.
The capture of samples they are even less frequent in the case of the patients walking or in the basic assistance - stated.
It is saved with disinfectants
The scientific experiments have shown that in the majority of cases the is a patient to another through the medical staff.
Therefore, they redeem a very important role the laundering of the hands, the use of gloves of rubber and masks, but also in this sense experience considerable lack in the hospitals.
The the is contaminated by means of transmission by drops, and the direct contact between people, but in the national hospital circumstances it is not always possible to isolate the patient infected.
Moreover, the rooms of hospitals, often are crowded, which are often are very together, although to prevent the epidemic, the patients should be separated, at least for a distance of metres.
Unfortunately, it is possible to experience also - karolina - that in the hospitals of economic situation less favourable was saved with disinfectants, there are few nurses and many patients, and for that reason there is a greater likelihood for the infection.
In view of, where it is complied with the appropriate measures of prevention, less infections of this type are registered or can stop the transmission of the pathogenic agent.
The government against the agenda
The treatment of infection with the is an enormous cost to the national fund of health insurance, so that in all the countries to fight against it.
In Britain for example there is a government programme to prevent and reduce the cases of the.
Apparently the programme is successful, according to the data provided, infection with the show trend of decrease in England.
The European Centre for the prevention and control of diseases () has among their priorities the prevention of the agents (among these the the) and of the hospital infections that due to these pathogenic agents.
