It has become the official expert report on the case of the fatal accident caused by the commander of the police of district XXII.
It is possible to exclude the possibility that drove drunken or stunned State since then resigned commander of the police of district XXII, who on Tuesday over and caused the death of one passer-by - reported on Friday Attila morvai, spokesman of the Prosecutor General of the capital, after having prepared the expert report on the case.
The expert report confirmed the result of primary control of blood alcohol that had already stated that the former - commander of the police consume alcoholic beverage before setting behind the wheel.
The leader of the time of the police station of the police of district XXII, on Tuesday with its particular vehicle to doubling the street kossuth lajos of district knocked down a 55-year-old man, who was trying to cross the street, but not in the area designated for pedestrians.
(this latter circumstance, that is to say, that the pedestrian did not use the zebra to cross the street, according to the provisions of the code of traffic are not mitigating circumstances, the driver must always yield to doubling.)
The passer-by was life after having been hospitalized.
For what happened to the police leader of the district resigned and requested his retirement, according to the release of the police, because it has affected a lot of the case.
The investigation of the case is the responsibility of the office of investigation of Budapest.
