The Czech Republic has the possibility of obtaining 365 billion
The Ministers of the government of the Czech Republic signed yesterday with representatives of the European Commission, a total of nine of the operational programmes that the Czech Republic can obtain 14 billion euros (approximately 365 billion Crowns).
It is practically half of the total sum that the Czech Republic can get to Brussels for the years 2007 to 2013.
Seven operational programmes will come to approximately 125 billion Crowns for the regions.
The Czech companies will be able to get around 100 billion Crowns of the company and innovation.
The greater part of the money will be devoted to the transport, up to 150 billion.
The agenda of transport is the largest of the operational programmes and accounts for up to 22% of the resources that the Czech Republic can obtain the fund.
This money is the budget of the State fund for railway transport that next year will be provided with the amount of 90,800 billion Crowns.
The agenda of enterprise and innovation must serve to entrepreneurs and businesses to the provision of resources in the development of the business.
The companies should obtain financing for the acquisition of new technologies, for the industrial research and for the implementation of more effective organizational methods.
As for the current use of the funds of the EU, the Czech Republic is among the countries newly less that use them.
