The banks to want to solve the crisis
The American Federal Reserve Bank, the European Central Bank and the central banks, British Swiss and Canadian decided to fight together against the crisis of the financial market.
In the monetary marked it will receive more than one hundred thousand million dollars through tenders.
In these tenders banks auction interest rates by which they are capable of giving money.
For example, the American fed will send to tender forty thousand million dollars, and other twenty-four thousand million will facilitate the central banks of Europe and Swiss.
After the attacks of 11 September, it is the first time that central banks of the different States come to an agreement in this process coordinated to protect and to diminish the consequences of the financial crisis.
"this step must solve the biggest economic problem, that is to say, the continuous growth of the shortage of free capital that banks might give" wrote in his report for the customers, Bernard baumohl of the company economic outlook group.
"the coordinated action of the central banks will probably decreased the recession in the United States from 65% to 50% added in his report.
The banks have already spent 60 billion in outstanding loans, especially in the United States.
Economists wait still billions in losses.
"the central banks should really have fear which it expects still when they decided to take this step," said the chief economist of ABN AMRO, kieran Davies.
"seems to be that the situation is really bad added.
The central banks fear that they have the same problems of access to loans and because it will have to give more expensive to its customers.
This would reduce the consumption and sends to the American economy in recession with different impacts on the growth of the world.
The central banks so decided, who did not manage to reduce the so-called tariff libor, tariff quarrels London that are used for the loan of money in the market.
This means that the banks feared constantly to lend money, even when the central banks of the USA, Canada and Great Britain reduced during the autumn its interest rates several times.
"will have the same effect as another drop in interest rates," said the Agency Reuters, Greg salvaggio of the company Tempus consulting.
Some economists are not surprised that the step taken by the central banks contributes to turning the crisis because it does not solve the basic problem that is the fall of the property market in the USA.
