The rest is made up of maximum resources planned for the Czech agency of consolidation with some 13,300 billion Crowns, the reservation of 10 billion Crowns for the payment of pensions, 43 billion Crowns to finance the obligations of the state and 1,800 billion Crowns in payments of the loans from the European Investment Bank.
