The President George Bush announced, for the opening of the conference of international peace met by it on Tuesday to annapolis, in Maryland, that the Israelis and the Palestinians had finally agreed on a common declaration.
He added that the Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Olmert and the Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas had agreed to open negotiations to find a definitive regulation of litigious point between his two peoples.
In the presence of both men, Bush promised that it would do everything to help them to conclude a peace treaty "before the end of the year 2008.
In the meantime, the Palestinians must dismantle "terrorists" infrastructures and Israel must put an end to its activities of colonization, Bush declared, reminding both sides to their obligations with regard to the itinerary to the peace that accepted in 2003.
The leader of the White House underlined that negotiations between Israel and the Palestinian Authority presided over by "Abbas would try to conclude a peace treaty that all the outstanding issues, without exception, including the central questions".
This denomination covers three main tricky problems of litigious point between Israelis and Palestinians: the future borders of Palestine, the status of Jerusalem and the fate of the Arab refugees expelled from their homes for the conflict in 1948.
Taking the word after the American President Abbas pressed for the coming negotiations are "global and aprofundizadas" and refer in all the aspects of a regulation, citing "Jerusalem, the refugees, the borders, the colonies, the water, the safety, among other things.
Rising to its turn in the tribunal, Olmert committed to what the coming negotiations are "direct and continuous" and "to make an effort to conclude in the trascurso of 2008.
Bush by the end of the year 2008 the term of the starting of his vision of two States "Palestinian and Israeli that coexist.
Saudi Arabia revealed that it had obtained a determination in this sense of part of Bush before deciding to take part in the Conference.
