Repair spectacular on the space station
It will have been needed more than seven hours of work in the space to astronaut Scott parazynski and his colleagues of the crew of the international space station (iss) to carry out the spectacular repair of a solar panel torn apart and essential for the continuation of the scientific activities of the station.
A dangerous departure that oversaw the records on account of its duration, its removal of the habitable modules, of the rapidity with which it has been imagined, instruments "bungled" for the astronauts for perform repair.
The problem appeared on Tuesday, then, that the astronauts had been released from the shuttle the module harmony, a heavy piece entrusted to receive prompt the European scientific laboratories and Japanese (see fit in).
This module is a type of platform of landing for the modules - laboratories.
But it is necessary to be able to be provided in electricity.
The second task of the crew was therefore move a module of electricity production with solar panels which weighed 17.5 tons, already present in the iss, with the aim of putting it in its final position.
After having been displaced, the crew started the reorganization of the solar panels of module that have a spread of 76 meters.
And this is where one of the panels, which are deployed as accordions, has been damaged in more or less of a meter by a cable that was blocked.
The deployment has been stopped for does not damage the panel more.
The astronauts, that they were the first to carry out a way out of control of the Shuttle, and then go to repair a solar panel, whose system of rotation was defective, were forced to be dedicated to the board damaged.
And it is Scott parazynski who has been elected to go to twist at the end of the 30 metres in length of remote-controlled arm of the shuttle added at the station to perform repair.
It is one of the best "spacewalker" (walking the space) of the basket.
High, resistant, very skilful, has the very developed and the long arms.
At the age of 46 years, this medical training since it has been entrusted to "produce" solar "wounded."
After having inspected precisely the damage, it cut the cable and installed types of "small" in the area damaged.
The second had helped him "spacewalker" that had been kept near the air, and of the Interior, by other astronauts as Peggy whitson, the commander of the crew.
The tool used, a minicane hockey surrounded with insulator to avoid electrocution in the solar panels that produced several hundreds of volts, has been conceived and "bungled" for the astronauts board of the station.
A time finished the operation, Scott parazynski waited for the panel to be completely opened before making the inventory of its instruments and return to the interior of the station.
Yesterday evening, the astronauts benefited from a rest noon earlier today, seven astronauts return of the shuttle for the return to the land foreseen on Wednesday.
