The Bank of England on Thursday was concerned to alleviate the present return of the concerns about the conditions of credit, and announced an offer of ten thousand million pounds to base index of 5.75% in five weeks, an offer of an unusual duration.
"to alleviate concerns according to which the conditions of the financial market will be particularly tight at the end of the year, and to give to the banks to a greater certainty in the way in which they will organize its positions of liquidity over this period, the Bank has the intention to offer an important proportion of its contribution of reserves anticipated during the period of maintaining that begins on 6 December in the form of an operation of open market for five weeks", indicates in a communiqué.
The Bank needs 10 billion pounds (14 billion euro) will be put on the market on 6 December to the 12 15 GMT, the rate of base and up to 10 January.
It is the first time it seems that the Bank inglaterro boe puts on the market liquidities for five weeks in an operation of open market.
These are normally made in a week.
The boe adds in its communiqué that "it is prepared to take other measures to support the indices" interbank loans to the day, in line with its base index.
The rate at the day was on Wednesday of 5.829%.
