My family doctor releases one of its articles on research rare entitled: 'the money causes, especially if the others receive less'.
That is to say, that the feelings that generates the monthly payment of workers depends on what the partners gain.
The study has been carried out by means of magnetic echoes in the University of Bonn, and the results are published in the last number of science.
According to Bernd Weber, author of the study and the director of the Group of image of neurocognición Institute of life & brain, in Germany: "the strongest activation took place when the participant responded correctly and his colleague failed".
Researchers observed that if when both succeeded received the same pay, the activation was a moderate, but if you received the double, the activation was greater.
I do not know if this conclusion required as much science.
