Sharks cards
The crisis of mortgages subprioritizes is infecting the American market of the credit cards?
When there are blood in the water, it is natural that a few numbers touched around.
Now that the American market of the House is in crisis, the predators have their eyes put on the market of the area of credit cards.
In goldman Sachs analysts estimate that the losses in credit cards can come to 99 billion if the crisis of mortgages subprime infected other forms of consumption credits.
Signs of infection already seen.
There is an increase in both the positions of cards as in the rates of crime, that the proportion of the balances that have not been or that they have more than 30 days delay respectively.
Hsbc announced last month that has taken 1.4 million position in its business of financing the American consumer, in part due to the weakness of the borrowers of cards.
However, it is too early to panic.
The slowness and crime are in low levels.
According to moody 's, an agency of qualification, the third quarter crime rate of 3,89% was almost a percentage point under the historical average.
The deterioration in the rates can be explained in part by technical factors.
A change in the law of the failure of the American people (2005) gave rise to a sharp decline in the applications of failure, which in turn represent a great loss in credit cards; the number of applications (and therefore, of dilatoriness) would be growing again, or it can happen that the conditions for the borrowers were getting worse.
The industry also brings solid rates of pay, which shows how much of their debts paid by consumers every month.
And the confidence in the credit cards and the values endorsed by assets is quite firm, in spite of the paralysis in other financial areas.
Dennis moroney of towergroup, a firm researcher, predicts that the volumes of emissions for the year 2007 will be around 25% higher than in the past year.
The direct channels of infection of the crisis between the subprime mortgages and the market of the credit cards certainly exists: consumers like to charge the debts to the credit cards that the credit organizations are expiring.
But the issuing of the credit card look more the flow of liquidity that the values assets, so that prices fall do not necessarily a change in the ability of the creditor borrowers.
Even they can work to the north.
The incentives for consumers continue paying off the mortgage decreases if the properties are worth less than the value of the loan; and, as a result, the payment of the debt of the card rises in the list of priorities.
The issuing of cards can also to respond quickly and flexibly to the difficult conditions that lenders mortgage interest rates, changing or altering balances creditors.
That in theory should reduce the risk of a rapid of assets.
"We are not going to wake up one day and evaluate all the loans again," says Gary perlin, head of capital finance one.
If a sudden infection of subprime into the market of the credit cards is unlikely, the risks of a sustained reduction are much more realistic.
If the prices of homes are lower and a credit crunch push to America to the recession, the industry undoubtedly faces a future more severe.
It is necessary to continue to keep these numbers.
British bankers convicted in Enron case
Three British bankers who went to court for his responsibility in the fraud with the previous leader of the financial office of Enron, Andrew fastow, were convicted this Wednesday.
David bermingham, Giles darby and Gary mulgrew were originally found innocent of seven positions of fraud because they were colluded with fastow in a secret financial operation in 2000 for rich at the expense of the employees.
They were sent to opinion in January.
But during the hearing before the judge Ewing werlein jr of district U.S, each one was sentenced as guilty of colución in fraud.
The three former executives of Greenwich natwest, a unit of the Scottish group plc in the Royal bank, became famous cause in Great Britain by the extradition procedures that lasted two years.
In the United States, its case marks the end of a loose Research sent after the collapse of Enron in 2001.
Initially, the charges against the bankers were to be alerted in 2002 fastow that was a target of a governmental research on the collapse of Enron.
The accusation against the bankers - "natwest three" - claims that came to Houston in 2000 to invent a fraudulent plan with fastow and his assistant over this, Michael kopper.
Greenwich natwest had invested in a subsidiary of a society of Enron controlled by fastow, that was the creator of a myriad of cheating in Enron, which helped to its spiral decline in failure.
In 2002, the Bank valued the interests of the subsidiary at zero, but the three British knew that he would in rise.
A company under the control of kopper bought the interest of bank of the subsidiary in $1 million dollars.
The bankers paid to kopper dollars by interests in this company.
According to the accusation, fastow represented falsely Enron, since the energy company would pay $20 million to Greenwich natwest by its parts of the subsidiary.
But the 20 million remained in the hands of the British bankers, fastow and others.
The bankers received millions, while fastow, kopper and other received near 12.3 million, according to the accusation.
In January 2004, fastow was sentenced guilty by two positions of conspiracy on the collapse of Enron.
The trio of British was arrested three months later.
Fastow is serving a sentence of 6 years in a federal prison of Louisiana.
Kopper is serving a sentence of 3 years, and a month in texarkana.
Each of the three British bankers must pay 1 million dollars needed to live in the United States as the judgment was celebrated.
Enron, one of the seven bigger companies of the nation, declared bankrupt in December 2001 after years of tricks in the accounting, would not be able to hide the debt of successful million or make it its business to fail.
The collapse did lose thousands of jobs, more than 60 million in stock market and more than two million in pension schemes.
