Venus: twin brother of the land.
In spite of its atmosphere is not adequate for life, Venus is the planet more similar to the land, which until now had not presented the European sounding "Venus express" discovered rays in the atmosphere and maelstrom in the Poles, such that it also appear in winter in the land.
Three decades ago researchers had the suspicion that could be rays in Venus.
But now the European sounding has brought new tests: discovered electromagnetic waves to the edge of the atmosphere. Cayen Venus the rays of a height of 54 kilometres of a cloud, and behind another, CRIS Russell of the University of California in Los Angeles in the scientific journal "nature".
According to the famous model of the origin of the life of urey-miller, the rays caused the life on earth: the storms could have provoked reactions in the ocean that, for its part, had given the amino acids that are the basic components of the life.
In Venus is not like this: if there were life there, that it should be one of the first states of evolution, explains are Solomon of the institution Carnegie of Washington.
Today, on the surface of Venus cannot be life: the atmospheric pressure is almost 100 times greater than in the land and the surface temperatures of 500 ° C, ranging from in such a way that they can be reached temperatures below zero.
"possibly, Venus is a" diabolical "of the land, but it remains a", said Russell.
The main objective of the mission "Venus express" is to respond to the question of why Venus, similar to the land by its mass and size, has had such a different evolution.
And since the 1990s were not special missions, only for research of this planet, the promotion of "venus-express" in November 2005 was a very important step for the investigation of Venus.
The results of the investigations that are going to be presented in many items of "nature", according to the opinion of the researchers, underline not only the uniqueness of Venus in the solar system.
This desmuestra also that the "planets have more common characteristics with the land of which we had course", that informs.
In spite of the already well-known stormy winds in the North Pole, researchers also discovered in the south polar region a vortex formed by the clouds that turns faster.
This phenomenon is reminiscent of the flows of wind in the high terrestrial atmospheres of the Poles, as it describes a team of researchers of Giuseppe piccioni of Italian Institute of special and space physics.
The second world of the solar system has the mass almost equal to the land and with its Equatorial diameter of 12 miles is almost so great.
This planet also called Star of dawn or evening star orbit around the sun almost 225 days.
But its period of rotation is slower: a day in Venus amounts to 243 days in the land.
Although Venus with their skin temperatures of 460 degrees and with its atmospheric pressure of 92 bars does not resemble a lot of the earth, the scientists depart from the basis that both planets had formed in the same conditions.
In the two planets had piled up water in the land remained in the oceans, but in Venus dissociated in the universe.
Whereas in the land carbon dioxide had become stones of carbon, in Venus form the greater part of the atmosphere.
